        "execSummary":  "Google\u0027s I/O 2026 keynote signals a decisive pivot from AI as a feature to AI as an autonomous operating layer ΓÇö Sundar Pichai declared the \u0027agentic Gemini era\u0027 and backed it with proof of scale: 3.2 quadrillion tokens processed monthly, 7x year-over-year. For enterprise leaders, this means Google\u0027s entire product surface ΓÇö Search, Workspace, Cloud ΓÇö is being reoriented around agents that take actions, not just answer questions. The introduction of Gemini Spark as a persistent personal agent and expanded API capabilities for managed agents suggests enterprise deployments will soon need governance frameworks for always-on AI actors. Leaders should assess how their organizations will manage agent identity, auditability, and escalation paths as these capabilities move from labs into production.",
        "vendorLean":  "Google",
