        "theme":  "Agents",
        "summary":  "Google announced expanded capabilities for Managed Agents in the Gemini API, including background execution for asynchronous tasks, remote Model Context Protocol (MCP) server integration, custom function calling, and credential refresh functionality. These features enable developers to build production-ready autonomous agents that operate within cloud sandboxes without blocking applications. The update makes it significantly easier to deploy agents that can work on long-running tasks independently.",
        "execSummary":  "Google is lowering the barrier for enterprise developers to ship production AI agents: background execution, MCP server integration, and credential refresh now come baked into the Gemini API\u0027s Managed Agents layer. This matters because the hardest part of agentic deployment is not the model ΓÇö it is safely managing async tasks, credentials, and external tool connections at scale. By abstracting these concerns into a managed infrastructure, Google is accelerating the path from prototype to production and competing directly with AWS Bedrock AgentCore and Microsoft Copilot Studio. Enterprise teams evaluating agent platforms should pressure-test how each vendor handles failure recovery, audit trails, and credential security before committing to an infrastructure.",
        "vendorLean":  "Google",
        "imageUrl":  null
