        "summary":  "Anthropic launched Claude Sonnet 5, its most agentic Sonnet model to date, designed to autonomously make plans, use tools like browsers and terminals, and handle complex multi-step tasks. The model delivers performance comparable to the more expensive Opus 4.8 at significantly lower cost, priced at $2/$10 per million input/output tokens. It features improved reasoning, tool use, coding, reduced hallucination rates, and real-time cyber safeguards enabled by default.",
        "execSummary":  "Claude Sonnet 5 is the most consequential enterprise AI model release of mid-2026: it matches the capability ceiling of Anthropic\u0027s flagship Opus model at a fraction of the cost, which fundamentally changes the economics of large-scale agentic deployment. For enterprise leaders, the combination of Opus-level reasoning, autonomous tool use, and introductory pricing at $2/$10 per million tokens makes high-volume production use cases economically viable for the first time. The built-in cyber safeguards and lower hallucination rates directly address two of the top barriers cited by enterprise risk and compliance teams. The caveat to watch: \u0027agentic\u0027 capability at scale requires robust human-in-the-loop governance, and enterprises should not assume safety defaults eliminate the need for their own oversight frameworks.",
